==== Basis and dimension ====
If the dimension of formula_1 is formula_76 and formula_77 is a basis for formula_1, then the set
: formula_79
is a basis for . The reason is the following: given any exterior product of the form
: formula_80
every vector formula_81 can be written as a linear combination of the basis vectors ; using the bilinearity of the exterior product, this can be expanded to a linear combination of exterior products of those basis vectors. Any exterior product in which the same basis vector appears more than once is zero; any exterior product in which the basis vectors do not appear in the proper order can be reordered, changing the sign whenever two basis vectors change places. In general, the resulting coefficients of the basis -vectors can be computed as the minors of the matrix that describes the vectors formula_81 in terms of the basis .

By counting the basis elements, the dimension of formula_73 is equal to a binomial coefficient:
: formula_84
where is the dimension of the &quot;vectors&quot;, and is the number of vectors in the product. The binomial coefficient produces the correct result, even for exceptional cases; in particular, formula_85 for .

