== Applications ==
=== Oriented volume in affine space ===
The natural setting for (oriented) formula_10-dimensional volume and exterior algebra is affine space. This is also the intimate connection between exterior algebra and differential forms, as to integrate we need a &#x27;differential&#x27; object to measure infinitesimal volume. If formula_286 is an affine space over the vector space {{tmath|V}}, and a (simplex) collection of ordered formula_287 points formula_288, we can define its oriented formula_10-dimensional volume as the exterior product of vectors formula_290 formula_291 (using concatenation formula_292 to mean the displacement vector from point formula_293 to formula_294); if the order of the points is changed, the oriented volume changes by a sign, according to the parity of the permutation. In {{tmath|n}}-dimensional space, the volume of any formula_76-dimensional simplex is a scalar multiple of any other.

The sum of the formula_296-dimensional oriented areas of the boundary simplexes of a {{tmath|k}}-dimensional simplex is zero, as for the sum of vectors around a triangle or the oriented triangles bounding the tetrahedron in the previous section.

The vector space structure on formula_119 generalises addition of vectors in {{tmath|V}}: we have formula_298 and similarly a {{math|&quot;k&quot;}}-blade formula_299 is linear in each factor.

